#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:3
#: bc0cb4f831b441a9a7729744c4ed83db
msgid "How to upgrade a Fedora template in-place"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:7
#: 70be8a544ecc472b91bf15cbd6511ca7
msgid "This page is intended for advanced users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:11
#: bcd472f38d07427b905c92b967212b6c
msgid ""
"**Warning:** This page is intended for advanced users only. Most users "
"seeking to upgrade should instead :ref:`install a new Fedora template "
"<user/templates/fedora/fedora:installing>`      . Learn more about the "
"two options :ref:`here <user/templates/fedora/fedora:upgrading>`      ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:13
#: bfbee01d400c4df18413654966e081a8
msgid ""
"This page provides instructions for performing an in-place upgrade of an "
"installed :doc:`Fedora Template </user/templates/fedora/fedora>`. If you "
"wish to install a new, unmodified Fedora template instead of upgrading a "
"template that is already installed in your system, please see the "
":doc:`Fedora Template </user/templates/fedora/fedora>` page instead. "
"(:ref:`Learn more about the two options. "
"<user/templates/fedora/fedora:upgrading>`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:16
#: 536be4da28514f848f10bbdf468d8ab0
msgid "Summary instructions for standard Fedora templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:19
#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:46
#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:169
#: 1bf25e1086204184a879a9efba2b7614 c2d3cc7572fb4c19af4d767a35861fd4
#: fb4590cdec9a42aaa2ad84272d0942f4
msgid ""
"**Note:** The prompt on each line indicates where each command should be "
"entered: ``dom0``, ``fedora-<old>``, or ``fedora-<new>``, where ``<old>``"
" is the Fedora version number *from* which you are upgrading, and "
"``<new>`` is the Fedora version number *to* which you are upgrading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:38
#: ede32e77c35e42fbbe97f31ccbfb95f9
msgid ""
"**Recommended:** :ref:`Switch everything that was set to the old template"
" to the new template. <user/templates/templates:switching>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:41
#: 46f98614d9414ac9903a18bb81444086
msgid "Detailed instructions for standard Fedora templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:44
#: f19343ca03564ab4a313d5537ed4f1dc
msgid ""
"These instructions will show you how to upgrade the standard Fedora "
"template. The same general procedure may be used to upgrade any template "
"based on the standard Fedora template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:48
#: 65c16ebfd061479c9f83014247fb4760
msgid "Ensure the existing template is not running."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:55
#: 81b0e5a67e454d3dbaeafaa22879bdd0
msgid "Clone the existing template and start a terminal in the new template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:63
#: 76718d396aad4e918c5ef279d4b054ea
msgid "Attempt the upgrade process in the new template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:71
#: 0b4523bc416b41b8a269e64cfc434cac
msgid ""
"**Note:** ``dnf`` might ask you to approve importing a new package "
"signing key. For example, you might see a prompt like this one:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:83
#: 23f360cb9df9457a9fdcc34a446f9062
msgid ""
"This key was already checked when it was installed (notice that the "
"“From” line refers to a location on your local disk), so you can safely "
"say yes to this prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:85
#: bf55d2184a2d47d8a93e87f3bbf934c9
msgid ""
"**Note:** If you encounter no errors, proceed to step 4. If you do "
"encounter errors, see the next two points first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:87
#: f7332166a6e8474b9c49ab902c8f1f19
msgid ""
"If ``dnf`` reports that you do not have enough free disk space to proceed"
" with the upgrade process, create an empty file in dom0 to use as a cache"
" and attach it to the template as a virtual disk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:95
#: b8bbaaa358b944ab808e750a1b3eeb4b
msgid ""
"Then reattempt the upgrade process, but this time use the virtual disk as"
" a cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:105
#: 243ca0462e7a433893a7ed48dd351c3c
msgid "If this attempt is successful, proceed to step 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:107
#: e1c38744b77d44a6ad3e2e2ea01992c8
msgid ""
"``dnf`` may error with the text: ``At least X MB more space needed on the"
" / filesystem.`` In this case, one option is to :doc:`resize the "
"template’s disk image </user/advanced-topics/resize-disk-image>` before "
"reattempting the upgrade process. (See `Additional Information "
"<#additional-information>`__ below for other options.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:112
#: 19915a958f3b4823aabf8baf573f1d96
msgid ""
"Check that you are on the correct (new) Fedora release. Do this check "
"only after completing the upgrade process. This is *not* a "
"troubleshooting procedure for fixing download issues from the repository."
" This check simply verifies that your clone has successfully been "
"upgraded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:120
#: 62d55cb206234abe833602bb9ce5536a
msgid ""
"(Optional) Trim the new template. (This should :ref:`no longer be "
"necessary <user/templates/templates:important notes>`, but it does not "
"hurt. Some users have `reported <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"issues/issues/5055>`__ that it makes a difference.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:130
#: 3669dce1e4ca40a489c421f24eff74f4
msgid "Shut down the new template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:137
#: f27f718f27a34c2e8a106191f69c4fb5
msgid "Remove the cache file, if you created one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:145
#: b4b89350287f4331ac6c10ed6ae48555
msgid "Set the template-name, which is used by the Qubes updater."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:152
#: 30f73429f6bf4164ac144a0d420d10a9
msgid ""
"(Recommended) :ref:`Switch everything that was set to the old template to"
" the new template. <user/templates/templates:switching>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:154
#: 8d7ec7986f0f49e6a39c8bf36b915f04
msgid "(Optional) Make the new template the global default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:161
#: cbe9454aecd94af9942de41929b5027e
msgid ""
"(Optional) :ref:`Uninstall the old template. "
"<user/templates/templates:uninstalling>` Make sure that the template "
"you’re uninstalling is the old one, not the new one!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:166
#: 01c99435b4bc490b8b98304e28aedc20
msgid "Summary instructions for Fedora Minimal templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:181
#: 78bdd858898345139a44e4df9b677a4a
msgid "(Shut down template by any normal means.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:183
#: 6ea9e6512d3f4fac9fb3a5693046c344
msgid ""
"(If you encounter insufficient space issues, you may need to use the "
"methods described for the standard template above.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:186
#: c82effa95e944690b0a93f1f48c10df7
msgid "Standalones"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:189
#: 09dda44a60af49369e8b00b493716a91
msgid ""
"The procedure for upgrading a Fedora :doc:`standalone </user/advanced-"
"topics/standalones-and-hvms>` is the same as for a template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:192
#: 3310385865a7416c8a1c788c1d3cbf15
msgid "Release-specific notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:195
#: 47ccfebaf7284b27b630c1a761e4aed9
msgid ""
"See the `news <https://www.qubes-os.org/news/>`__ announcement for each "
"specific template release for any important notices about that particular"
" release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:198
#: f32816dc3c324a639cccad27617b458f
msgid "End-of-life (EOL) releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:201
#: 0a01e1cb55ce43d082b9e2e04689df24
msgid ""
"We strongly recommend against using any Fedora release that has reached "
"`end-of-life (EOL) <https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/End_of_life>`__. Also "
"see :doc:`supported releases </user/downloading-installing-upgrading"
"/supported-releases>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:204
#: 9d7a659113f6447bb0e0c1885503ea54
msgid "Additional information"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:207
#: 90e7d946aadc487aa7ed05c950ac4ed5
msgid "As mentioned above, you may encounter the following ``dnf`` error:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:215
#: f517e8da4a90476d95a4784721b72a58
msgid "In this case, you have several options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:217
#: 4f522c13d8524b5ea694e0405d801b72
msgid ""
":doc:`Increase the template’s disk image size </user/advanced-topics"
"/resize-disk-image>`. This is the solution mentioned in the main "
"instructions above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:219
#: 139b32fb28cf4c96b09bd85896181339
msgid ""
"Delete files in order to free up space. One way to do this is by "
"uninstalling packages. You may then reinstall them again after you finish"
" the upgrade process, if desired). However, you may end up having to "
"increase the disk image size anyway (see previous option)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:221
#: 3fb422030191406aa0daf3f27c4ee2bc
msgid ""
"Do the upgrade in parts, e.g., by using package groups. (First upgrade "
"``@core`` packages, then the rest.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/fedora/fedora-upgrade.rst:223
#: 43f754c44e6b4070bdcef08ee918078f
msgid ""
"Do not perform an in-place upgrade, see :ref:`Upgrading Fedora templates "
"<user/templates/fedora/fedora:upgrading>`."
msgstr ""

